Turkish authorities have captured the gunman who killed 39 people in a mass shooting at an Istanbul nightclub on New Year&#8217;s Day after a two-week nationwide manhunt, Prime Minister Binali Yildirim confirmed on Tuesday.State-run Anadolu news agency earlier said the alleged attacker, whom it and other media named as Abdulgadir Masharipov, was detained in Istanbul&#8217;s outlying Esenyurt district.-Reuters